-- Greek-German Bond Yield Spread Surpasses 800 Points, Highest Since Oct. 1
-- B y   L u k a n y o   M n y a n d a
-- 2010-10-29T08:16:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/greek-german-bond-yield-spread-surpasses-800-points-highest-since-oct-1.html
Greek 10-year bonds  weakened for a
fifth consecutive day, pushing the extra yield investors demand
to hold the securities instead of benchmark German bunds above
800 basis points for the first time since Oct. 1.  The yield increased 15 basis points to 10.64 percent as of
9:11 a.m. in London. The spread over bunds was at 801 basis
points from 688 basis points on Oct. 22.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lukanyo Mnyanda in London at 
 lmnyanda@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
